264
00:19:13,593 --> 00:19:14,423
Hello.

265
00:19:15,002 --> 00:19:16,907
- Welcome.
- Here comes a great actor.

266
00:19:16,907 --> 00:19:18,972
- Master comedian!
- Long time no see.

267
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:22,010
- Master, can I have a corn dog?
- Sure.

268
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:26,160
- I'll take your coat.
- Thanks.

269
00:19:31,809 --> 00:19:35,945
We were worried about you
since you hadn't come for a while.

270
00:19:35,945 --> 00:19:40,005
Sorry about that.
I've been very busy these days.

271
00:19:40,005 --> 00:19:42,057
We watch your drama every week.

272
00:19:42,057 --> 00:19:43,976
I'm so grateful.

273
00:19:43,977 --> 00:19:46,342
You know that thing?
The bird thing?

274
00:19:46,342 --> 00:19:47,926
- You mean Twitter.
- That's it.

275
00:19:47,926 --> 00:19:52,686
Young fans use that
to comment on my acting.

276
00:19:53,211 --> 00:19:55,934
Some of them even show up
to our comedy theater to see me.

277
00:19:55,935 --> 00:19:57,731
Wow!

278
00:20:03,265 --> 00:20:04,385
Welcome.

279
00:20:16,165 --> 00:20:18,085
- Beer, please.
- Sure.

280
00:20:20,581 --> 00:20:22,541
Not only fans,

281
00:20:23,211 --> 00:20:26,761
but a movie director
also saw my performance.

282
00:20:27,261 --> 00:20:30,431
He wants me to play a role
in his new movie.

283
00:20:30,613 --> 00:20:33,743
Awesome.
This must be the big break of your career.

284
00:20:34,944 --> 00:20:37,194
I don't want to retire yet.

285
00:20:37,565 --> 00:20:40,405
I must compete with young men

286
00:20:40,912 --> 00:20:43,872
for jobs and women.

287
00:20:50,270 --> 00:20:51,110
Here you go.

288
00:20:55,607 --> 00:20:56,697
This is for you.

289
00:20:57,894 --> 00:20:59,484
It's on Serao.

290
00:21:00,075 --> 00:21:00,999
Hey, Master...

291
00:21:02,180 --> 00:21:04,270
I have no reason to treat that jerk.

292
00:21:05,494 --> 00:21:08,034
Well, you do have a reason.

293
00:21:10,898 --> 00:21:11,898
Your drama gig...

294
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:15,750
was set up by Hajime.

295
00:21:18,643 --> 00:21:20,005
You are lucky...

296
00:21:21,334 --> 00:21:23,294
to have such a nice pupil.

297
00:21:42,769 --> 00:21:43,889
Thank you.

298
00:21:45,031 --> 00:21:49,077
Are you big enough
to influence the casting now?

299
00:21:49,077 --> 00:21:52,087
That's not true.
It was just a slip of the tongue.

300
00:21:52,456 --> 00:21:55,876
I'm too old to handle a lot of gigs.

301
00:21:56,377 --> 00:21:59,025
I won't allow you to retire yet.

302
00:21:59,025 --> 00:22:00,974
Are you sure about that?

303
00:22:00,974 --> 00:22:04,054
Soon I will take all the gigs
away from you.

304
00:22:04,677 --> 00:22:06,307
Really? Then try me.

305
00:22:08,431 --> 00:22:12,141
Well, this is enough.
I'll take mercy on you for now.

306
00:22:14,867 --> 00:22:18,573
Once the batter puffs up,
roll it with chopsticks.

307
00:22:18,834 --> 00:22:20,544
That way you can fry it evenly.

308
00:22:21,351 --> 00:22:24,068
The batter is good not just for sweets,

309
00:22:24,068 --> 00:22:26,805
but also some other ingredients.
You should try it.

310
00:22:26,805 --> 00:22:27,635
Here you go.

311
00:22:28,998 --> 00:22:31,248
Deep-fried fish sausage. Bon appétit.

312
00:22:34,206 --> 00:22:35,126
It's so good.

313
00:22:36,234 --> 00:22:38,074
- Can I have some?
- What?

314
00:22:38,793 --> 00:22:40,873
- Just a bite, please.
- No way.

315
00:22:41,335 --> 00:22:43,617
Who do you think you are, asshole?

316
00:22:43,617 --> 00:22:45,302
Good night.

317
00:22:45,302 --> 00:22:48,682
Hey, give me some.

318
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:45,926
THIS STORY IS A WORK OF FICTION

